  "text": "A 5-plex PCR was performed to detect the tcdA, tcdB, cdtA, and cdtB genes and 16S rDNA [CITATION_1] . C. difficile strain ST1/RT027 (tcdA + , tcdB + , ctdA + , ctdB + ) was used as a positive control for the amplification. The conditions and primers for the PCRs were as previously reported with several modifications [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The PCR assay was performed at 94°C for 10 min, followed by 32 cycles of 94°C for 50 s, 57°C for 40 s, and 72°C for 50 s, and a final extension at 72°C for 10 min.",
